    <h2 id="why-acne-gummies">The Internal Factors That Drive Acne (And How Gummies Address Them)</h2>

    <p>Acne is fundamentally an inflammatory condition with multiple internal drivers that topical treatments alone cannot fully address. While cleansers, retinoids, and benzoyl peroxide manage surface-level bacterial colonization and pore clogging, the internal factors that trigger and sustain acne — systemic inflammation, gut microbiome imbalance, mineral deficiencies, and hormonal sebum dysregulation — require internal intervention. This is where acne-targeted supplements enter the treatment picture, providing the nutritional building blocks and microbiome support that the skin needs to reduce breakout frequency and severity from the inside out.</p>

    <div class="key-stat">
