      <div class="info-card"><div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="leaf" size={22} /></div><strong>Gut-Skin Axis</strong><p>Probiotics restore gut microbiome balance, reduce intestinal permeability, and decrease systemic inflammatory markers (CRP, IL-6, TNF-alpha) that drive skin inflammation and acne. Lactobacillus and Bifidobacterium strains have the strongest acne evidence.</p></div>
      <div class="info-card"><div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="target" size={22} /></div><strong>Keratinocyte Regulation</strong><p>Vitamin A normalizes the turnover rate of skin cells (keratinocytes), preventing the dead cell accumulation that combines with sebum to clog pores. This addresses the comedonal (blackhead/whitehead) component of acne at the cellular level.</p></div>
      <div class="info-card"><div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="droplet" size={22} /></div><strong>Sebum Balance</strong><p>Zinc and vitamin A together reduce excess sebum production and normalize its composition, creating a less favorable environment for acne-causing bacteria while maintaining the healthy lipid barrier the skin needs for protection.</p></div>
    </div>

